summary=["There's a psychological impact overall, but there's also a direct impact on companies like Sony and TDK which derive a high percentage of their earnings from overseas markets,'' said PelhamSmithers, a stock strategist in Tokyo at ING Baring Securities Japan Ltd A new survey in Japan said confidence among small- and medium-sized businesses about the economy plunged to its worst level since the Bank of Japan began the quarterly samplings in 1967"]